Task 1: Fork the Repository
•	Fork the given repository to your GitHub account.
•	This can be done by navigating to the original repository and clicking on the "Fork" button.

Task 2: Add a File to Add Two Numbers
•	Clone the forked repository to your local machine.
•	Create a new file named "add_numbers.py" in the cloned repository.
•	Write a Python program in the "add_numbers.py" file to add two numbers and print the result.
•	Commit the changes with an appropriate commit message.

Task 3: Create a Branch
•	Create a new branch in the repository.
•	The branch can be named anything you prefer.
•	Switch to the newly created branch to work on the next task.

Task 4: Create a File to Display Your Name
•	In the newly created branch, create another file named "display_name.txt".
•	Inside the "display_name.txt" file, write your name.
•	Commit the changes with an appropriate commit message.

Task 5: Generate a Pull Request
•	Push the branch with the added files to your forked repository.
•	Go to the original repository on GitHub and create a new pull request.
•	Select your branch as the source branch and the main repository as the destination branch.
•	Provide a brief description of the changes made and submit the pull request.




GLHF
